{"cursor":"9858","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"Facilitation}} A 'facilitator' is someone who helps a group of people understand\ntheir common objectives and assists them to plan to achieve them without taking\na particular position in the discussion. Some facilitator tools will try to\nassist the group in achieving a consensus on any disagreements that preexist or\nemerge in the meeting so that it has a strong basis for future action.\n","linknr":153,"url":"Facilitator","recorded":1362890573,"links":22,"instances":["business"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Meetings","Management","Group processes"],"headings":["Definitions","Authority","Types","Skills","See also","Bibliography","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["facilitation","business"],["facilitation","business"]],"members":["facilitation"],"related":["Consensus_decision-making","Synergy","John_Heron","Mediation","Moderator","Arbitrator","Progressive_stack","Progressive_stack","Consensus_decision-making","Facilitation_(business)","Business","Hierarchical_organisation","Empowerment","Adult_education","Dialogue","Group_dynamics","Social_group","International_Association_of_Facilitators","Facilitation_(business)"]}